OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FClaudette Colvin: Civil    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Frights pioneer has record  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fcleared                    
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Civil rights activist Claudette Colvin,
OL,6, who in 1955 at age 15 refused to give  
OL,7, up her seat on a bus for a white       
OL,8, person, has had her record expunged.   
OL,10,F"My name was cleared," Ms Colvin told  
OL,11,FCBS News, the BBC's US partner. "I'm no
OL,12,Flonger a juvenile delinquent at 82."   
OL,14,FMs Colvin was convicted of assaulting a
OL,15,Fpolice officer while being arrested in 
OL,16,FAlabama and put on probation.          
OL,18,FAfter a petition from Ms Colvin, an    
OL,19,FAlabama judge last month ordered the   
OL,20,Frecords to be destroyed.               
